<subSubSection pageId="6" pageNumber="135" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,1748,2028]" pageId="6" pageNumber="135">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,322,1820,1847]" pageId="6" pageNumber="135">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Tibial spur well developed; one strong vibrissa; two pairs of prescutellar setae; anepisternum bare, with a black spot; fore coxa with three long setae anteriorly.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="7" lastPageNumber="136" pageId="6" pageNumber="135" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,1748,2028]" box="[199,862,1892,1920]" pageId="6" pageNumber="135">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,345,1892,1919]" pageId="6" pageNumber="135">Description.</emphasis>
Body length, 
<quantity box="[503,606,1892,1920]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.95" pageId="6" pageNumber="135" unit="mm" value="2.95">2.95 mm</quantity>
. Wing length, 
<quantity box="[768,857,1893,1920]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.4" pageId="6" pageNumber="135" unit="mm" value="2.4">2.4 mm</quantity>
